1
00:00:00,958 --> 00:00:02,708
At exactly 12 midnight

2
00:00:04,083 --> 00:00:08,291
We heard a sound in the wall near the window

3
00:00:08,666 --> 00:00:12,166
It seemed like an escape attempt was happening

4
00:00:13,458 --> 00:00:18,333
We stayed anxious because we
didn’t know what was happening outside

5
00:00:19,250 --> 00:00:22,583
When I was in the far group cell

6
00:00:23,083 --> 00:00:26,416
I knew there was a place easy to escape from

7
00:00:27,458 --> 00:00:29,750
The prison was basically a basement

8
00:00:29,958 --> 00:00:32,791
With a small breathing window above

9
00:00:33,208 --> 00:00:36,416
Completely reinforced with iron protection

10
00:00:37,291 --> 00:00:38,666
But that group cell

11
00:00:38,916 --> 00:00:40,625
Had an external staircase

12
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:42,750
Which they had recently sealed off

13
00:00:43,333 --> 00:00:44,916
Using concrete blocks

14
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:48,375
It was sealed tightly

15
00:00:49,916 --> 00:00:51,166
But if someone thought and worked carefully

16
00:00:51,250 --> 00:00:52,375
It was possible to escape from there

17
00:00:53,125 --> 00:00:54,666
I noticed a solid iron object outside

18
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:58,041
When my cousin and I were preparing to escape

19
00:00:58,166 --> 00:01:00,041
During a time when my relatives were being released regularly

20
00:01:00,166 --> 00:01:02,708
We thought our turn for release was coming soon

21
00:01:04,708 --> 00:01:06,375
But we decided to escape

22
00:01:06,625 --> 00:01:08,166
Unfortunately, they transferred us to a different cell

23
00:01:08,291 --> 00:01:09,958
When I was with my father, I told him

24
00:01:10,041 --> 00:01:12,541
That we had planned to escape from that group cell

25
00:01:17,833 --> 00:01:21,041
My father was with a young man named Ahmad Seno

26
00:01:21,791 --> 00:01:24,041
And another young man named Hamad

27
00:01:27,833 --> 00:01:30,583
I had spoken to them about my plan to escape through that cell

28
00:01:31,375 --> 00:01:32,875
It seems they remembered my words exactly

29
00:01:32,958 --> 00:01:35,083
Saying, This is the cell he talked about

30
00:01:35,333 --> 00:01:39,416
And that this was where the
external door had recently been sealed

31
00:01:40,166 --> 00:01:41,916
They also saw the same iron piece

32
00:01:42,083 --> 00:01:43,958
I had told them about, so they decided to escape

33
00:01:45,625 --> 00:01:47,083
I realized that they were escaping

34
00:01:47,625 --> 00:01:49,000
The next morning after the escape

35
00:01:50,541 --> 00:01:53,916
There was great chaos inside the prison

36
00:01:54,083 --> 00:01:56,375
They distributed special prison uniforms to us

37
00:01:56,541 --> 00:01:58,375
They took all our civilian clothes

38
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:00,125
They also gave us numbers

39
00:02:00,625 --> 00:02:02,333
And searched for any iron objects

40
00:02:02,833 --> 00:02:06,083
They installed surveillance cameras in the prison

41
00:02:08,166 --> 00:02:10,041
Then one of them came and asked me, What’s your name?

42
00:02:10,416 --> 00:02:12,000
I answered, Faraj Salamah

43
00:02:12,333 --> 00:02:14,375
He asked, Is your father’s name Khalaf?

44
00:02:14,541 --> 00:02:17,125
I said yes, and he told me that
my father had escaped from prison

45
00:02:18,041 --> 00:02:20,291
I had suspected that all that noise was because of an escape

46
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:23,416
And that the escape had happened from our same group cell

47
00:02:23,583 --> 00:02:25,083
But I didn’t know who they were at the time

48
00:02:25,333 --> 00:02:27,625
Yet when my father’s voice grew distant, I thought

49
00:02:27,708 --> 00:02:29,166
He must have been in that faraway cell

50
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:31,583
I pretended to the one asking that I
was upset about my father’s escape

51
00:02:31,708 --> 00:02:36,041
Because no charges had been
proven against us for three months

52
00:02:36,708 --> 00:02:39,666
My father had endured prison and
nothing had been proven against him

53
00:02:40,083 --> 00:02:44,041
So it didn’t make sense for him to escape and leave us behind

54
00:02:45,250 --> 00:02:47,375
Inside, I prayed to God to help him succeed

55
00:02:49,041 --> 00:02:52,500
He told me they would catch him wherever he was

56
00:02:52,708 --> 00:02:56,500
Whether in Turkey or in Germany

57
00:02:58,708 --> 00:03:01,083
I told him I wasn’t responsible for his escape

58
00:03:01,208 --> 00:03:02,791
I was in one group cell and he was in another

59
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,333
He said, You’re not to blame

60
00:03:04,708 --> 00:03:06,250
What we want is for you to call your uncles

61
00:03:07,125 --> 00:03:09,958
And tell them you’ll be killed if your father doesn’t return

62
00:03:11,083 --> 00:03:14,333
I told him I didn’t know their numbers

63
00:03:14,458 --> 00:03:15,916
But he kept insisting

64
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:18,166
So I said, As you wish, but bring me one of their numbers

65
00:03:18,375 --> 00:03:24,541
A day and then two passed without him coming back
